From Tuesday night at midnight it jumps to R21.60 a litre inland, that's an increase of R1.46. Peter Morgan, the CEO of the liquid Fuel Wholesalers Association, spoke with eNCA's Sally Burdett about the increase. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Expect long queues at fuel pumps on Tuesday night. Motorists will be rushing to fill up before the petrol price goes up by R1.46 cents at midnight. READ: Higher oil prices could hike up petrol price The diesel price will rise by at least R1.44 and paraffin users will be hard hit as the wholesale price will jump by R1.21. The retail price will be up by as much as R1.61. READ: Massive petrol price hike expected for March The inland price of unleaded 95 petrol is now the highest it's ever been at R21.60. The price increases are chiefly due to higher international oil prices. Analysts say April could also see a steep hike as the Russian-Ukraine conflict pushes oil prices higher.